        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 1:30AM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 130 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Pageland to near Horrel Hill. Movement was
northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Sumter, Camden, Cheraw, Bishopville, Shaw Air Base,
McEntire Air Base, Lake Wateree Dam, Pageland, Chesterfield,
Eastover, Lugoff, Oakland, Fort Jackson, Westville, Cheraw State
Park, Hopkins, Northeastern Technical College, Cassatt, and Cheraw
Municipal Airport.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 77 and 121.
Interstate 26 between mile markers 119 and 121.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 5 and 10.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
